  "response": "To see who is following you on Snapchat:\n\n1. Open the Snapchat app\n2. Tap on your profile icon in the top left corner\n3. Look at the number next to \"Friends\" or \"Followers\"\n4. To see the specific list of followers:\n   - Tap on \"Friends\" or \"Followers\"\n   - This will show you the complete list of people who follow you\n\nIf you want to see who added you recently:\n- Go to your Friends list\n- Look for people with a \"Added you\" tag\n\nNote: Unlike some social media platforms, Snapchat doesn't always make it very obvious who is following you, and the visibility depends on your privacy settings.",
